<br>
Is this a bug or is this intended, since it seems like a tradeoff between criting a lot during the battle (SCF3) or nearly guaranteeing a crit at the finish blow (SCFM1)?<br>
<br>
<br>
For example, I quad in ME at Toiler hill.  During an average quad, I cast pillar of flame and get from 6 to 10 crits throughout the battle with SCF3.  Now, when I upgrade to SCFM1, I get from 0 to 1 crits during the battle, but the finishing blow kill shot gets crits nearly 70% of the time.<br>
<br>
Also now, Ice comet and Draught of ice blasts rarely give crits now in CT, which is really annoying since I was criting a great deal before.  However, again about 50-70% of the kill shots crit.  Arggggh, I want to go back to SCF3!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uenoah35.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/7/02 6:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmm</span><hr size=1> Well SCF line increases the damage of the crit I heard. SCFM however increases the chance of critting. Wierd that never happend to me. Altho I have noticed no increase between SCFM 1 and 2. 3 however I crit alot now with SCFM3. <br>
